import os import json import shutil import numpy as np from PIL import Image import matplotlib.pyplot as plt  plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 150  img_path = './RWTReid/todo/' target_path = './RWTReid/done/' files = os.listdir(img_path) files.sort() num_todo = len(files) if os.path.exists('./RWTReid/data_captioned.json'):     json_path = './RWTReid/data_captioned.json' else:     json_path = './RWTReid/data_info.json' with open(json_path, 'r') as f:     all_list = json.load(f)  print(json_path, 'loaded successfully.')      print('========================= Welcome! =========================') cnt = 0 for pic_name in files:     print('************************************************************')     data_dict = all_list[pic_name]     print(' @ Person ID:', data_dict['id'])     print(' @ Image Path:', data_dict['img_path'])     print(' @ Captioned/Todo: %d/%d' % (cnt, num_todo))          img = Image.open(img_path + pic_name)     plt.imshow(img)     plt.axis('off')     plt.show()          while True:         caption = input('===> Input Caption:\n')         if len(caption.split(' ')) < 20:             print('Your caption ought to be no shorter than 20 tokens. Please try again.')             continue                      is_ok = input('===> Finish this caption? (N/n to rewrite, any other key to continue)')         if is_ok != 'n' and is_ok != 'N':             all_list[pic_name]['captions'].append(caption)             shutil.move(img_path + pic_name, target_path + pic_name)             cnt += 1             with open('./RWTReid/data_captioned.json', 'w') as f:                 json.dump(all_list, f)             print('===>', pic_name, 'is captioned successfully!')             break              print('\n************************************************************') print("===> You have done today's work! Thanks for you contribution!")
